cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.DB

This paper discusses the challenges and future research areas for digital forensic investigation, which involves computer security (cs.CR), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), cybercrime (cs.CY), software engineering (cs.SE), and databases (cs.DB). The paper specifically focuses on the technical aspects of digital forensics, such as identification, acquisition, storage, and analysis of digital evidence, which are relevant to these sub-categories.
